{
  "stem": "14060.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In other words, to limit the Jewish population or basically eradicate it over the generations without killing them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was immediately a consistent emigration from these provinces into other parts of the Austro-Hungarian Empire.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the story goes that our family moved in the early 1800s from there into western Hungary, come Burgenland, which is the area where we lived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in fact, there is a famous seven communities, Sheva Kehillot, which many people know about in the eastern part of Austria-- Burgenland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And those communities were basically populated and established by the Esterhazy family, who were very liberal to Jews and held very large estates on both sides of the border in Austria and Hungary.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know that one of the rogues of the family was the Esterhazy involved in the Dreyfus Affair.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was actually, as far as the family was concerned, a throw-out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the family, as such, were decent to Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they allowed them to settle in these seven communities.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were certain restrictions.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't all that free for all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were many raids by the Catholic Church, where they were trying to grab children and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a very personalized history of my Weiler grandmother, whose maiden name was Heitler, that there was a child, apparently, who lost his parents at a very early age.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the local Catholic priest tried to pressure, as a community, that as the child has got no guardian, they want to take the child into care.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they put him with a non-Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, at the end, protestations went to Vienna to the, at the time, kaiser, or whoever was in charge.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
